### Leaders as Mentors

The responsibility of organizational leaders to mentor the next generation of leaders is crucial

Mentorship is an extension of stewardship as the most important resource a leader has is human resource

Helping people continually improve their performance is an important aspect of leadership, one of the best ways to achieve this is through mentoring

Mentoring provides numerous benefits for both individuals and the organization as a whole, including facilitating relationship building, promoting communication, enhancing performance, and developing the next generation of leaders

**Best practices in mentoring:**
- Setting a positive example
- Establishing clear learning milestones
- Fostering effective and regular communication
- Encouraging critical thinking and innovation
- Empowering prodigies
- Providing inspiration, support, and encouragement